- OpenGL -- Open Graphic Library [wikipedia]

+ Cross language Application programming interface (API)
+ Renders 2D and 3D vectors
+ Multi plateform
    - CPU, GPU, digital signal processors (DSP), field-programmable fate arrays (FPGA) and other processors. 
+ Open standard maintained by the Khronos Group

-- WebGL -- Web graphic Library [wikipedia]

+ Javascript API to OpenGL
+ Rendering interactive 3D & 2D graphics within the browser without using plugins.
+ Khronos

-- OpenCL -- Open Computing language [wikipedia]

+ Framework 
+ Special derived C language.
+ Multi plateform.
+ Khronos

-- WebCL -- [khronos.org]

+ Javascript API to OpenCL framework.
+ Enables web application to use GPU and multicore CPU parallel processign from within a web browser.
+ Enables significant acceleration of application 
    - Image and video processing for WebGL games.
+ Kronos
